{
  "texts": [
    "Diffusion models for image generation have recently gained substantial attention 8, [28] [29] [30].",
    "Researchers continue to improve the performance of diffusion models, making them new mainstream generative models and demonstrating excellent image-generation capabilities [30] [31] [32].",
    "A diffusion model mainly consists of a diffusion module and a denoising module.",
    "The diffusion module converts the input raw image into a noisy image by continuously adding noise.",
    "This is followed by a denoising module, which restores the noisy image to the original image."
  ]
}